name: dockerized-microservices-backend-order-system
description: Implemented product, order, and customer services with service discovery (Eureka) and API Gateway. Dockerized services for seamless deployment, using H2 database.

name: healthcare-system-config
description: The configuration of Healthcare System with Spring-boot microservices

name: eng-microservices
description: English application based on Microservices Architecture intergrate with NLP model as SpaCy. The system puts a string emphasis on load-balacing capacity using technology such as: Kafka,  Eureka (discovery service)

name: Blog_Microservice
description: This repository contains a gRPC-based Blog Microservice written in Protocol Buffers (proto3). The service allows users to create, read, update, delete, and list blog posts. The service is designed for scalability and can be integrated into larger systems for managing blog content.

name: SkyConnect
description: This is an Airline management and flight booking system based on microservices architecture.

name: JFSD-Microservices-SDP-S12-18
description: FRONTEND for below description33. JFSD-PS33: Develop a student feedback and evaluation systemCreate a web application to collect and analyze student feedback on courses, instructors, andinstitutional services. The system should provide insights and data to help improve the educationalexperience and address areas for improvement.

name: decomp-rldec
description: This project is an implementation of the RLDec decomposition approach as described in the paper "Extracting Microservices from Monolithic Systems using Deep Reinforcement Learning"

name: patipada-search
description: This repository is source code  of dhammanava search system (Waris's Senior Project), the architecutre is Microservices.

name: d2-slack-architecture
description: This project is an architecture of real-time messaging system similar to Slack, designed using a microservices architecture.

name: Custom-API-gateway
description: Custom API gateway for microservices with rate limiting, authentication, load balancing, caching and API analytics. Multiple authentication methods (OAuth, JWT, API key). Challenge: designing and building scalable API systems, security layers and request throttling strategies for microservice architectures.

name: e-commerce
description: An e-commerce distributed System microservices architecture built using Spring Boot and Spring Cloud, leveraging Kafka for messaging, MongoDB for data storage, and Zipkin for distributed tracing.

name: movie-app
description: The Movie App System is a distributed application composed of multiple microservices designed to provide various functionalities related to user management, movie data retrieval integrated with IMDB movie API, and Wishlist management.

name: EcommercePlatform
description: A scalable and robust e-commerce platform built using microservices architecture. This project leverages Go as the primary programming language and implements a variety of modern technologies and practices to create a flexible and efficient online shopping system.

name: User_Management_App
description: A microservices-based architecture with two Spring Boot applications: one for user and profile management, and another as a Backend for Frontend (BFF) service. The system is integrated with PostgreSQL using Docker and communicates between services via REST APIs.

name: user_crud
description: This project represents the second exam of the Microservices course, developed using FastAPI, a modern framework for building APIs in Python. The main goal is to create a user management system that allows performing CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on user information.

name: document-based-gpt
description: This is a project for a document-based GPT system that allows users to upload documents, and later query these documents. The solution is built using a microservice architecture, and employs a vector store (FAISS) for document embeddings, allowing fast retrieval of relevant content based on user queries.
